@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}
<main aria-labelledby="title">
    <h2 id="title">@ViewBag.Title.</h2>
    @*<h3>@ViewBag.Message</h3>*@

    <h4>Overview</h4>
    <p>
        The ASP.NET MVC Pharmacy Management System is a web application designed for Suma Pharmacy to automate inventory and sales operations. It replaces manual record-keeping with a central system, improving efficiency and accuracy. The system allows staff to record purchases and sales, track stock in real time, and generate reports through a user-friendly interface.
    </p><br />
        <strong>Key Features</strong>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>Purchase Management: Record new stock purchases; inventory quantities update automatically.</li>
                <li>Sales Processing: Log sales transactions (prescriptions and OTC items); inventory is adjusted accordingly.</li>
                <li>Interactive sales bar chart to visualize revenue over time.</li>
                <li>Generate inventory reports (stock levels, expirations) and transaction reports on demand.</li>
                <li>User & Role Management: Support for multiple user roles (Administrator, Pharmacist, Cashier) with appropriate permissions.</li>

            </ul>
            <br />
            <strong>Technologies Used</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Backend Framework: ASP.NET MVC with C# (built in Visual Studio Community).</li>
                <li>Frontend Libraries: DevExtreme UI components (JavaScript/HTML/CSS) for responsive interface.</li>
                <li>MySQL for storing products, inventory, and transactions.</li> 
                <li>Git for version control, jQuery (as required by DevExtreme), and standard web technologies (Bootstrap, etc.).</li> 

            </ul>
            

        </p>
</main>